WEBVTT

00:00.218 --> 00:01.268
<i>We knew our lives</i>

00:01.269 --> 00:02.635
<i>would never be the same.</i>

00:02.637 --> 00:03.836
<i>He saved my life.</i>

00:03.839 --> 00:05.310
<i>And she saved mine.</i>

00:05.311 --> 00:07.411
<i>We're destined.</i>

00:07.413 --> 00:08.996
<i>But we know it won't be easy.</i>

00:08.998 --> 00:11.949
<i>Even though we have</i>
<i>every reason to stay apart...</i>

00:11.951 --> 00:14.334
<i>We'll risk it all</i>
<i>to be together.</i>

00:14.336 --> 00:17.004
I am so in love with you.

00:20.441 --> 00:22.742
<i>Previously on</i>
Beauty & the Beast:

00:22.744 --> 00:25.679
I have been hunting Muirfield
for most of my life.

00:25.681 --> 00:28.098
So you were some kind
of guinea pig?

00:28.100 --> 00:29.449
Continually being harvested

00:29.451 --> 00:31.534
for blood and tissue

00:31.536 --> 00:33.453
and anything else
they could take from me.

00:33.455 --> 00:35.058
I still don't know
what you want with me.

00:35.083 --> 00:35.790
You're a cop.

00:35.791 --> 00:37.924
My position can
open certain doors,

00:37.926 --> 00:40.677
but you can go places
that I can't.

00:40.679 --> 00:43.263
If we work together, we can
take Muirfield down for good.

00:43.265 --> 00:45.248
I thought you'd be
more sympathetic

00:45.250 --> 00:47.350
to someone who was
used by Muirfield.

00:47.352 --> 00:51.137
I will be if he really is
who he says he is.

00:51.139 --> 00:52.439
That woman I told you about?

00:52.441 --> 00:54.090
The one who smuggled
me out of Muirfield?

00:54.092 --> 00:56.943
I think she might have been
Detective Chandler's mother.

00:56.945 --> 00:59.529
♪

01:00.648 --> 01:07.537
♪ Gonna wash the dust
off my soul ♪

01:07.539 --> 01:10.206
♪ Gonna listen
to some rock and roll... ♪

01:10.208 --> 01:11.774
Good morning.

01:11.776 --> 01:13.376
Hey.

01:13.378 --> 01:15.495
How long have you been here?

01:15.497 --> 01:16.896
Uh, a little while.

01:16.898 --> 01:18.832
You're just watching
me sleep?

01:18.834 --> 01:20.133
Yeah, there's a lot to watch.

01:20.135 --> 01:22.585
You, uh, you did this yawn

01:22.587 --> 01:24.120
and then you did this

01:24.122 --> 01:26.139
little cute
nose scratch thing,

01:26.141 --> 01:29.643
and then, uh, you did
that, uh...

01:29.645 --> 01:31.394
You know, that-that
clucking noise that you make.

01:31.396 --> 01:32.646
I do not cluck.

01:32.648 --> 01:34.564
Oh, yeah, you do.
No.

01:34.566 --> 01:36.850
♪ That waves will wash
the gray away ♪

01:36.852 --> 01:40.270
♪ I'm making
a beautiful day... ♪

01:40.272 --> 01:42.138
You know, I just...

01:42.140 --> 01:45.608
I didn't want you
to wake up alone today.

01:45.610 --> 01:47.077
You okay?

01:47.079 --> 01:49.312
Yeah.

01:49.314 --> 01:51.915
I mean, my mom has
been gone ten years.

01:51.917 --> 01:53.500
It doesn't matter
how long it's been,

01:53.502 --> 01:55.318
an anniversary
is always hard.

01:55.320 --> 01:57.570
This year feels different.

01:57.572 --> 02:01.091
Different good
or different bad?

02:01.093 --> 02:04.874
Well, you're here,
so that's good.

02:04.899 --> 02:05.296
Hmm.

02:05.297 --> 02:08.798
And I'm not waking up
racked with guilt.

02:08.800 --> 02:12.552
Well, it's the first year
you know you're not responsible.

02:12.554 --> 02:16.439
Yeah, but I'm not responsible
because Muirfield killed her

02:16.441 --> 02:18.024
because she worked with them.

02:18.026 --> 02:20.343
The people that
ruined your life...

02:20.345 --> 02:21.945
My life is far
from ruined.

02:21.947 --> 02:24.514
...who are hunting you
down, she was one of them.

02:24.516 --> 02:27.784
She was one of the good ones.

02:27.786 --> 02:31.621
Okay, so, a little different bad

02:31.623 --> 02:33.456
and good, yeah?

02:33.458 --> 02:36.159
More bad than good.

02:36.161 --> 02:38.628
Which is why I really
don't feel like celebrating

02:38.630 --> 02:41.464
her celestial
birthday tonight.

02:41.466 --> 02:43.032
Her what?

02:43.034 --> 02:44.634
Family tradition.

02:44.636 --> 02:46.753
The idea was,
when she dd,

02:46.755 --> 02:49.255
she was born to the stars.

02:49.257 --> 02:52.642
So, we get together,
light candles,

02:52.644 --> 02:54.427
listen to her
favorite music,

02:54.429 --> 02:55.979
eat her favorite food.

02:55.981 --> 02:58.348
Well, sounds nice.

02:58.350 --> 03:01.317
Except even though we know
she liked '80s power ballads

03:01.319 --> 03:03.236
and pineapple on her pizza,

03:03.238 --> 03:06.806
turns out we didn't
really know her at all.

03:06.808 --> 03:08.742
She lied to me.

03:08.744 --> 03:11.795
And I was her person,
we were so close.

03:13.948 --> 03:15.749
So...

03:15.751 --> 03:18.067
You know what I want
to celebrate tonight?

03:18.069 --> 03:19.669
What?

03:19.671 --> 03:21.671
Our anniversary.

03:21.673 --> 03:24.507
You realize that that's
today, too, don't you?

03:24.509 --> 03:29.212
Yes, the anniversary
of the first time

03:29.214 --> 03:30.746
we saw each other.

03:30.748 --> 03:33.516
Of the first time
you saved me.

03:33.518 --> 03:37.437
So, I'm just gonna tell
Heather and my dad

03:37.439 --> 03:41.357
that I'm busy, and,
um, you and I can...

03:42.810 --> 03:44.310
No, no, no, no, no.

03:44.312 --> 03:46.279
Bailing on your dad
and your sister

03:46.281 --> 03:48.865
is just gonna make you
feel guilty all over again.

03:48.867 --> 03:51.734
Okay, besides, it seems
like you need reminding

03:51.736 --> 03:54.037
that you did know her,

03:54.039 --> 03:56.289
at least
in the important ways.

03:56.291 --> 03:58.641
Yeah, favorite pizza
topping is so important.

03:58.643 --> 04:00.293
Come on,
let's not get caught up

04:00.295 --> 04:03.112
in the bad stuff
from the past.

04:03.114 --> 04:06.249
Today is about
celebrating her

04:06.251 --> 04:07.550
and moving forward.

04:07.552 --> 04:09.302
Right, moving forward.

04:09.304 --> 04:12.305
Which is why I want
to celebrate us.

04:12.307 --> 04:14.507
Uh-uh.

04:14.509 --> 04:16.341
Mm, okay, we can do that

04:16.344 --> 04:18.310
by going
to the cemetery together,

04:18.313 --> 04:20.512
and saying hi to her.

04:20.515 --> 04:22.232
♪ And it's gonna be
my beautiful day... ♪

04:22.234 --> 04:24.934
Well played.

04:24.936 --> 04:26.469
Hey.
Hey, Vargas,

04:26.471 --> 04:28.655
I, uh, I want to go
over the security detail

04:28.657 --> 04:30.690
for the mayor's thing today.
Oh, right, yeah,

04:30.692 --> 04:33.660
there's a lot of details
about the detail.

04:33.662 --> 04:35.695
Listen, I want to apologize
to you for bailing this morning.

04:35.697 --> 04:36.996
I mean, who knew that Marelli

04:36.998 --> 04:39.199
got his morning coffee
near your place?

04:39.201 --> 04:41.751
That was a really good save,
saying that you were checking out

04:41.753 --> 04:42.919
a new gym.
Mm.

04:42.921 --> 04:44.120
I'd believe that we just

04:44.122 --> 04:46.539
ran into each other
if I was him.

04:47.842 --> 04:51.261
Or maybe I should just learn
how to make coffee.

04:51.263 --> 04:53.930
Or we could just go public.

04:53.932 --> 04:55.765
Wow.

04:55.767 --> 04:57.383
Okay.

04:58.802 --> 05:00.937
Tess, there's a spot
open at the 15th.

05:00.939 --> 05:02.555
You would transfer for me?

05:04.109 --> 05:05.608
The spot is for you.

05:07.344 --> 05:10.813
Wow, so you just assumed
that I'd be the one to go?

05:10.815 --> 05:13.283
There aren't as many spots
available at my level.

05:13.285 --> 05:14.534
Right.

05:14.536 --> 05:16.069
But I've worked
my ass off to get

05:16.071 --> 05:17.487
the respect I get
at this precinct.

05:17.489 --> 05:18.821
Yeah, and if
people found out,

05:18.823 --> 05:20.039
you could lose
that respect.

05:20.041 --> 05:22.792
Me?

05:22.794 --> 05:24.210
Both of us.

05:24.212 --> 05:25.879
It was just a suggestion.

05:25.881 --> 05:28.248
Okay, like you said,

05:28.250 --> 05:30.049
we covered with Marelli.

05:30.051 --> 05:31.751
We don't have
to go public.

05:31.753 --> 05:33.386
It's up to you.

05:35.422 --> 05:37.390
I only have an hour

05:37.392 --> 05:39.259
before I have to
be security detail

05:39.261 --> 05:41.394
for the mayor's
park dedication.

05:41.396 --> 05:43.313
Moving forward, remember?

05:43.315 --> 05:45.098
Right.

05:45.100 --> 05:47.317
Let's go give her some lilies.

05:47.319 --> 05:51.104
See, it's just like
we're walking in Central Park.

05:51.106 --> 05:53.573
Hey, we don't get to do that.

05:55.109 --> 05:56.659
What?

05:56.661 --> 05:57.827
Who is that?

05:57.829 --> 05:59.329
Is that Gabe?

05:59.331 --> 06:01.063
What is he doing here?

06:01.065 --> 06:02.999
Well, did you tell him
what today was?

06:03.001 --> 06:04.233
No.

06:04.235 --> 06:05.752
Maybe Tess or Joe did?

06:05.754 --> 06:09.172
So, what, he's paying
his respects?

06:09.174 --> 06:12.258
He was a victim of Muirfield,
and he knows she was, too.

06:12.260 --> 06:13.509
Or maybe he has a thing for you.

06:13.511 --> 06:14.677
What?

06:14.679 --> 06:16.179
Well, you just spent

06:16.181 --> 06:17.413
all that time together

06:17.415 --> 06:18.464
looking over Muirfield files.

06:18.466 --> 06:19.432
Yeah, that was

06:19.434 --> 06:21.017
really romantic.
Well, maybe

06:21.019 --> 06:22.218
he thought it was.

06:22.220 --> 06:24.187
He doesn't know you got

06:24.189 --> 06:25.355
a boyfriend.

06:25.357 --> 06:27.023
Just... we'll
come back later.

06:27.025 --> 06:28.924
No, I am busy later.

06:28.926 --> 06:30.893
Don't you want to know
what he's doing here?

06:30.895 --> 06:34.397
Besides, you're the one who
made this convincing argument

06:34.399 --> 06:36.733
that I should start my
day saying hi to my mom.

06:36.735 --> 06:39.068
And now you want me
to blow her off?

06:39.070 --> 06:41.154
Okay, I'll wait until he's gone.

06:41.156 --> 06:43.122
Give me the calla lilies.

